# Project Basic Rules

This document outlines the fundamental rules and guidelines for the project. All contributors must adhere to these rules to maintain consistency and quality.

## Communication

- Primary language for code and documentation: English
- Use GitHub Issues for bug tracking and feature requests
- Discussions and planning happen in Discord

## Tech Stack

- Package Manager: pnpm
- Framework: Next.js v15+ (React)
- Language: TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4+
- Component Library: shadcn/ui, Magic UI, Tailark
- Animation: Framer Motion
- Internationalization: next-intl

## Coding Style

- Follow the code style guidelines defined in code-style.mdc
- Use ESLint and Prettier for linting and formatting

## Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `UserProfile`)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., `getUserData`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`)
- Files: kebab-case (e.g., `user-profile.tsx`)
- i18n Keys: dot notation (e.g., `page.home.title`)

## Error Handling

- Always handle errors gracefully
- Log errors with sufficient context for debugging

